    ("Maximum sustainable yield (MSY) for fisheries is at approximately:", ["N = K (carrying capacity)", "N = K/2 (half the carrying capacity)", "N = 0", "N = 2K"], 1, "Maximum growth rate occurs at roughly K/2."),
    ("Mark-recapture methods estimate population size using the formula:", ["N = total catch", "N = (M × C) / R, where M=marked, C=recaptured sample, R=recaptured marked", "N = birth rate × death rate", "N = area × density"], 1, "Lincoln-Petersen method."),
    ("Metapopulation theory considers:", ["only one isolated population", "a set of spatially separated populations connected by dispersal", "genetic diversity within a single individual", "only extinct populations"], 1, "Subpopulations exchange individuals via migration."),
    ("Source-sink dynamics occur when:", ["all habitats are equally productive", "some habitats produce surplus individuals (sources) that colonize less productive areas (sinks)", "migration never occurs", "all populations grow exponentially"], 1, "Sources export; sinks would decline without immigration."),
