    ("Population viability analysis (PVA) estimates:", ["market value of fish stocks", "the probability of population persistence over a given time period", "salinity changes", "nutrient concentrations"], 1, "PVA assesses extinction risk."),
    ("Leslie matrix models use _____ to project population growth.", ["only birth rates", "age-specific survival and fecundity rates in a matrix format", "ocean current data", "single population counts"], 1, "Matrix multiplication projects age-structured populations."),
    ("In marine ecology, r-selected species tend to have:", ["few offspring with extensive parental care", "many small offspring, fast maturation, and short lifespan", "very large body size", "low reproductive output always"], 1, "High reproduction, low parental investment."),
    ("K-selected species in the ocean tend to have:", ["many small offspring", "few large offspring, slow maturation, long lifespan, and parental care", "no predators", "unlimited resources"], 1, "Whales, sharks, sea turtles are K-selected."),
