    ("Deuterostomes develop the anus first from the blastopore; examples include:", ["insects and crabs", "echinoderms and chordates", "sponges only", "cnidarians and flatworms"], 1, "Deutero = second; stoma = mouth."),
    ("Segmentation (repeated body units) is seen in:", ["cnidarians only", "annelids and arthropods", "sponges only", "echinoderms"], 1, "Segmental body plans allow regional specialization."),
    ("Exoskeletons (in arthropods) vs. endoskeletons (in echinoderms) differ in that exoskeletons:", ["are internal", "are external and must be shed for growth", "allow unlimited growth", "are made of bone"], 1, "Exoskeleton = external; growth requires molting."),
    ("Gas exchange in marine invertebrates occurs through:", ["lungs in all species", "gills, skin diffusion, tube feet, or specialized structures depending on the group", "only through mouths", "stomata"], 1, "Different groups evolved different respiratory structures."),
